I was imagining if we could do the following:
Iterator<HiveFileInfo> iterator = delegate.list(...);
if (cachedTableNames.contains(schemaTableName)) {
  return cachingIterator(iterator, path); 
}
return iterator;

And then we also change cachingRemoteIterator to:
Iterator<HiveFileInfo> cachingIterator(Iterator<HiveFileInfo> iterator, Path path) {
  return new Iterator<HiveFileInfo>() {
    private final List<HiveFileInfo> files = new ArrayList<>();
    ...
  };
}

The reason I'm asking is that the current design does not really go through the delegate DirectoryLister when we need to leverage cache. Let me know what you think :) Besides this, all looks good!

